olive oil
2 clove garlic
1 stalk celery
1 bunch spring onion
½ carrot
1 tin sweetcorn
2 packet Peeled Prawns
1 packet Korean Stir-Fry Sauce
1 bag Shredded Cabbage Mix
1 tsp sesame oil
drizzle vinegar (rice wine or white wine)
1 packet sriracha
1 packet mayonnaise

• Finely chop garlic. Thinly slice celery and spring onion. Grate carrot (see ingredients). Drain the
sweetcorn.
• In a large bowl, combine peeled prawns, garlic and a drizzle of olive oil. Set aside.

• Heat a large frying pan over medium-high heat. Cook sweetcorn, tossing, until lightly browned,
4-5 minutes. Transfer to a large bowl.

TIP: Cover the pan with a lid if the corn kernels are "popping" out.

• Return the frying pan to medium-high heat with
enough olive oil to coat the base.
• When oil is hot, cook prawns in batches, tossing, until pink and starting to curl up, 3-4 minutes.

• Wipe out the frying pan, then return to medium heat with a drizzle of olive oil.
• Add Korean stir-fry sauce and a splash of water, and cook, stirring, until heated through, 1 minute.

• Meanwhile, add shredded cabbage mix to the charred corn, along with carrot, celery and a drizzle of sesame oil and vinegar. Season with salt and pepper and set aside.
• In a small bowl, combine sriracha and mayonnaise. Season to taste.

• Divide charred corn slaw between bowls. Top with prawns.
• Spoon Korean sauce over the prawns.
• Drizzle with sriracha mayo and garnish with spring onion to serve. Enjoy!